<h2>Science and the Modern World: Questions and Answers</h2>
<p><strong>1. What is the role of science in the modern world?</strong></p>
<p>Science is an essential component of the modern world. It has been responsible for numerous advancements that have improved our lives, such as electricity, the computer, and the Internet. Science also helps us understand the natural world and our place in it.</p>
<p><strong>2. What are some of the benefits of science?</strong></p>
<p>Science has led to numerous benefits for humanity, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>Improved health and longevity</li>
<li>Increased agricultural productivity</li>
<li>Development of new technologies</li>
<li>Understanding of the natural world</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>3. What are some of the challenges posed by science?</strong></p>
<p>Science can also pose challenges, such as:</p>
<ul>
<li>Environmental degradation</li>
<li>Nuclear weapons</li>
<li>Ethical dilemmas</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>4. How can we ensure that science is used for good?</strong></p>
<p>We can ensure that science is used for good by:</p>
<ul>
<li>Investing in science education</li>
<li>Funding scientific research</li>
<li>Promoting scientific literacy</li>
<li>Engaging in dialogue about the ethical implications of science</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>5. What is the future of science?</strong></p>
<p>The future of science is bright. New technologies and discoveries are constantly being made. Science is expected to play an increasingly important role in the years to come, as we continue to face new challenges and opportunities.</p>